additional_house_rules:
Note:  please understand that this house is not suitable and not equipped to accommodate infant (under age 2 or new born). If you have additional guests (stay over night) later during your stay, you have to let us know. 


1)  Quiet hour after 11PM and before 7AM, daily

2) No incense and smoking inside the house. Please only use the candle in the candle holder we provide.

3) No loud music and jumping on the floor , please respect other guests on first floor, as they do the same.

4) Please wear the sandals we provide when you and your guests enter the house. They are located in the first floor entry, more can be found on 2nd fl walk in closet outside the stairway.

5) Please put everything back to the way it was, and close all windows when you leave the building.

6) We use keyless lock only ( code will be provided to guests for their stay). Please do not touch other locks on any doors, that might lock you and your guests out. 

7) For guests stay longer than 3 weeks. We provide one complimentary house clean up (2 hours), including vacuum and steam moped all floor, clean all table/desk tops, change all bed linens/sheets/towels. Please contact the host to arrange the date.


8) Please separate trash according to the picture instruction on the refrigerator between trash and recycles and leave them in separate trash bins at the ground entrance to the house.

9) Welcoming our guests, we provide complimentary snacks/breakfast/fresh fruits on the day of the arrival! Enjoy!


Relax and Enjoy your stays in this beautiful home!
description:
This cozy home is 6 minutes walk from R Train with 30 minutes commute to lower Manhattan and 45 minutes to middle Manhattan. It's one block away from the famous  Bay Ridge restaurants street- third avenue-Grotto, Tanoreen and Grand Sichuan House, just name a few. It's also 5 minutes walk away from Century 21. You’ll love my place because of the location, the people, the neighborhood, and the ambiance. My place is good for couples, solo adventurers, business travelers, and families. Book today!

This is the second floor of a two family house.  The total floor space is around 800 sqf.

You have full access to the whole second floor apartment, including two bedrooms, sitting room, kitchen with gas stove, microwave, coffee machine, refrigerator and essential cooking utensils and dishware, bathroom and the office room. There is high speed wifi access/wire internet and wireless TV for your entertainment. All these are private for you without sharing with any other parties. The entrance to the second floor is external and separate from the first floor.

Our level or frequency in connection wth you depend absolutely on your preferences.

This lovely neighborhood is one of the most convenient and safest community of NYC. It's close to shopping, restaurants, laundry and subways!

6 minutes walk to R Train, 30 minutes to lower Manhattan and 45 minutes to Midtown by Subway. If you are interested in visiting New Jersey, Pennsylvania and Connecticut, it's one to two hours drive via Verrazano bridge, avoiding all the traffic of Holland tunnel or Lincoln tunnel.

There is the famous Shore Road Park  6-7 blocks away from our house, Verrazano Bridge is about 15-20 minutes walk away, you'd fall in love with the sunset view and taking a jog along the shore will be a guaranteed memorable experience.

Love shoppings? You don't need to go to Manhattan. The following popular stores are just 5-10 mins walk from our property!!!

Century 21st, Bath & Body works, Victoria's Secret, Banana Republic, Modell's, New York & Company, T.J.Maxx,  Gap, The Children's Place,
